    "Specifically, we rationalize the source knowledge k into verbalized form to generate k ′.",
    "Then, we provide (s, k ′) with the predefined label set T and prompt the LLM to re-assign type t based on the evidence k ′.",
    "An example of knowledge-grounded evidence is provided in Figure 5.",
    "Based on provided definition and semantic type of the candidate \"mononuclear leukocytes\", LLM generates a knowledge-grounded evidence and assigns type to the candidate.",
    "If the knowledge is irrelevant to the domain, the LLM will assign t as NONE."
